        <comment>PMID: 21900390 DOI: 10.1158/1078-0432.CCR-11-1155

BRAFV600E has been shown to initiate thyroid follicular cell transformation. The BRAFV600E mutation disrupts the hydrophobic interaction, enabling the BRAF kinase to fold into a catalytically active formation, resulting in an almost 500-fold increase in kinase activity. Mutant BRAF can dimerize and activate MEK without Ras activation.</comment>
