    <edge id="FOXD3:EGFR" from="FOXD3" to="EGFR" minvalue="1" sign="negative">
      <annotation>
        <comment>www.impactjournals.com/oncotarget/
Oncotarget, 2017, Vol. 8, (No. 3), pp: 5048-5056

CRC

Here, we first showed that FOXD3 knockdown dramatically increased the proliferation of human colon cancer cells, enhanced cell invasive ability and inhibited cell apoptosis.

Silencing FOXD3 markedly activated EGFR/Ras/Raf/MEK/ERK pathway in human colon cancer cells. In addition, blocking EGFR effectively
decreased the activity of MAPK induced by FOXD3 knockdown. In human cancer tissue, the expression of FOXD3 was reduced, however, the EGFR/Ras/Raf/MEK/ERK pathway was activated. Our study indicates that FOXD3 may play a protective role in human colon formation by regulating EGFR/Ras/Raf/MEK/ERK signal pathway.</comment>
      </annotation>
